  "stem": "<figure class=\"table\"><table border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\" scope=\"col\"><math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math></th>\n<th style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\" scope=\"col\"><math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"negative 12\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn>\n</math></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"negative 45\"><mo>-</mo><mn>45</mn>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn>\n</math></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.701%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"45\"><mn>45</mn>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></figure>\n<p>The table shows two values of <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> and their corresponding values of <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math>. The graph of the linear equation representing this relationship passes through the point <math alttext=\"left parenthesis one fourth comma a right parenthesis\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>. What is the value of <math alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
